Mónika Hoke from Bellevue, Wash., is a graduate student in Chemistry through the Knight Campus Graduate Internship Program. This summer, Monika is working as an intern with the team that contributes to the characterization of the hyper-elastic polymer gel used in Purple brand mattresses and seat cushions.
“The process of scientific discovery excites me, and each day we continue to define the characteristics and push the limits of the unique properties of our polymer," Mónika says. "As my career develops, I hope to continue discovering new material applications, maybe even the next greatest car seat cushioning.” #uosummer

The Overlook Field School is an immersive summer design studio for UO students. They use fieldwork and art methods to investigate an annual theme, culminating with the construction of landscape installations.

The theme this year? Recovery. The work centers around mega fires, the demonization of controlled burning and general climate events. 

Summing up the program, the students said, “Despite the prevailing narrative of catastrophe and destruction, the recovery we observed has been incredibly inspirational. We aspire to communicate these experiences through landscape installations so that we may remember the beneficial impacts of fire throughout increasingly longer fire seasons.”
 
Tap link in bio for more info on the Overlook Field School.
